  "prompt": "What happens if you overdose on Naproxen?",
  "response": "An overdose of naproxen, a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID), can lead to serious health complications. Symptoms of a naproxen overdose may include:\n\n- Nausea and vomiting\n- Stomach pain\n- Dizziness or lightheadedness\n- Headaches\n- Tinnitus (ringing in the ears)\n- Drowsiness or lethargy\n- Diarrhea\n- Abdominal bleeding\n\nIn severe cases, an overdose can result in more serious conditions, such as kidney damage, gastrointestinal bleeding, respiratory distress, or even life-threatening effects. \n\nIf an overdose is suspected, it is crucial to seek immediate medical attention or contact a poison control center. Treatment may involve supportive care to manage symptoms, and medical professionals may perform treatments such as gastric lavage or administering activated charcoal if the overdose is recent.\n\nAlways use medications like naproxen according to the prescribed dosage and consult with a healthcare professional if you have any questions or concerns.",
